8,http://www.armslist.com/posts/44008,"For Sale:  Remington 1100 20ga 3"" magnum","clinton, Arkansas, United States",$ 350,"Listed On: Friday, July 23, 2010",Shotguns,Remington                                                                                ,no type,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Shotgun,"am selling off a few guns from the back of the safe to finance another project. Here is a 20ga 1100LW 3INCH MAGNUM. You will not see many 1100 magnums in 20ga. Blueing is at atleast 95% wood is a lighter color with the normal little nicks and digs you will have with a gun that has been in the field. The only downside to this gun is the barrel has been cut down to 22 1/2 inches with a thin wall choke system installed and I only have one choke .It is marked IC ,, It patterns great with buckshot and #4 nitro mags. You can get more chokes from any of the bigger choke companies like Brileys or Tru-Choke but a REMCHOKE WILL NOT FIT. I bought this gun years back when I was going to Iowa pheasant hunting several times a year and this gun patterned so well I just never bothered to get more chokes.This is a great bird/field gun. It is set up for a sling so you can sholder it on all those long walks in the fields and recoil is light enough for a good deer gun for a kid. $350 Clinton ar."
